                <note rend="inline" type="source">781.003/249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-11T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 11, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 11—noon.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>970. My 957, July 8, 7 p.m., first paragraph. The Foreign Office states that in
                    the commercial treaty with France regarding Morocco the British only dealt with
                    subjects normally covered in British commercial treaties and these subjects do
                    not cover state monopolies or exchange control. These questions therefore did
                    not arise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
